    <div id="content" class="clearfix">
          
  <div id="div-gpt-ad-4397870-9"></div><div class="content work-body-wrapper"><div class="DesignSystem"><div class="onsite-ping" id="onsite-ping"></div></div><div class="DesignSystem swp-content moar-logged-in-swp-sidebar moar-swp-sidebar-attachment"><div class="js-swp-left-column-content swp-left-column-content w_responsive"><div class="js-swp-left-column-top-content"><div class="DesignSystem u-bgColorWhite expanded-top-card--container"><div class="clearfix js-parent work_1946455" data-work_id="1946455" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/ScholarlyArticle"><div class="expanded-top-card--content u-pb6x"><div class="js-swp-work-title col-xs-12 col-md-12 u-fontSerif u-fw100 u-fs28 u-lineHeight1_3 u-ph0x u-mb3x"><div class="u-workBreakBreakAll"><span itemprop="name">Muhammad Reza Pahlavi and the Bahrain Question, 1968–1970</span></div></div><div class="col-xs-12 col-md-9 u-fs13 u-ph0x u-tcGrayDarker u-mb2x">British journal of Middle Eastern studies, 2010</div><div class="col-xs-12 col-md-12 u-ph0x"><a class="js-profile-link media_v2 expanded-top-card--card-profile-link" data-has-card-for-user="2525279" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20220418015302/https://lse.academia.edu/RohamAlvandi?swp=tc-au-1946455"><div class="media-left media-middle u-pr1x"><img class="Avatar--circle s65 Avatar--circle s65 Avatar--xxxs" alt="Roham Alvandi" shape="circle" border="0" onerror="if (this.src != '//a.academia-assets.com/images/s65_no_pic.png') this.src = '//a.academia-assets.com/images/s65_no_pic.png';" width="65" height="65" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20220418015302im_/https://0.academia-photos.com/2525279/787026/17850048/s65_roham.alvandi.jpg"/></div><div class="u-pl0x media-right media-middle SWPCoauthorPopover-ListItemMediaBody u-fw500 u-tcGrayDarkest"><div class="u-textTruncate"><span itemprop="author">Roham Alvandi</span></div></div></a><div class="hidden-xxs"><div class="work-metadata-wrapper u-mt2x"><div class="work-metadata-container clearfix"><p class="js-expanded-card-work-details--abstract">This paper examines the role of Muhammad Reza Pahlavi, the late Shah of Iran, in the secret Anglo-Iranian negotiations over Bahrain from January 1968 to March 1970. Despite a clear strategic imperative for abandoning Iran&#39;s claim to Bahrain in the wake of the British withdrawal from the Persian Gulf, the Shah feared that such an act would be seen by the Iranian public as collusion with the British to surrender Iranian territory, thereby further eroding the Pahlavi monarchy&#39;s precarious legitimacy. Drawing on British official papers and Iranian oral histories and memoirs, this paper explores for the first time the story of these secret negotiations and the extent to which the Shah&#39;s diplomacy was constrained by domestic considerations.</p><div class="js-expanded-card-work-details--extra-details u-displayNone"><div class="metadata has_taggings"><h6 class="metadatum"><strong>Publisher: </strong>Taylor &amp; Francis</h6><h6 class="metadatum"><strong>Publication Date: </strong>Jan 1, 2010</h6><h6 class="metadatum"><strong>Publication Name: </strong>British journal of Middle Eastern studies</h6></div></div><a class="js-expanded-card-work-details--more u-tcBlue u-clickable">Show more&nbsp;▾</a><a class="js-expanded-card-work-details--less u-clickable u-tcBlue u-displayNone">Show less&nbsp;▴</a></div></div></div><div class="hidden-xxs"><ul class="WorkInfo u-listStyleNone u-listInline u-mt3x u-mb0x"><div class="u-displayInlineBlock u-mb2x"><div class="clickable u-fs14"><span class="expanded-top-card--ri-bubble href"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20220418015302/https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Diplomatic_History?swp=tc-ri-1946455">Diplomatic History</a></span></div></div><div class="u-displayInlineBlock u-mb2x"><div class="clickable u-fs14"><span class="expanded-top-card--ri-bubble href"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20220418015302/https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/The_Persian_Gulf?swp=tc-ri-1946455">The Persian Gulf</a></span></div></div><div class="u-displayInlineBlock u-mb2x"><div class="clickable u-fs14"><span class="expanded-top-card--ri-bubble href"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20220418015302/https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/History_of_Iran?swp=tc-ri-1946455">History of Iran</a></span></div></div><div class="u-displayInlineBlock u-mb2x"><div class="clickable u-fs14"><span class="expanded-top-card--ri-bubble href"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20220418015302/https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/British_Imperial_and_Colonial_History_1600_-_?swp=tc-ri-1946455">British Imperial and Colonial History (1600 - )</a></span></div></div><div class="u-displayInlineBlock u-mb2x"><div class="clickable u-fs14"><span class="expanded-top-card--ri-bubble href"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20220418015302/https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Bahrain?swp=tc-ri-1946455">Bahrain</a></span></div></div></ul></div><div class="hidden-xxs"><ul class="u-listStyleNone u-fs12 u-tcGrayDarker u-pl0x u-listInline u-mt2x u-mb0x u-mr4x"><li class="swp-hide-for-mobile-logged-out"><span><span class="js-view-count view-count u-mr2x" data-work-id="1946455"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin"></i></span></span></li><li class="js-swp-header-paper-rank hidden swp-hide-for-mobile-logged-out"><span class="js-paper-rank-view hidden" data-paper-rank-work-id="1946455"><span class="u-mr2x">•</span><span class="u-mt0x">PaperRank: </span><span class="js-paper-rank u-mr2x"></span></span></li><li class="swp-hide-for-mobile-logged-out js-percentile-container"><span class="percentile-widget hidden"><span class="u-mr2x percentile-widget" style="display: none">•</span><span class="u-mr2x work-percentile"></span></span></li><li><div class="js-viewable-attachments-button" data-placement="bottom" data-toggle="popover"><span class="u-mr2x">•</span><span class="clickable"><span class="js-viewable-attachments-preview-index"></span>2 Files<i class="fa fa-caret-down u-fs12 u-ml2x"></i></span></div><div class="js-viewable-attachments-popover-content hidden"><div class="u-p2x"><div class="js-preview-attachment-button u-tcGrayDarkest" data-preview-attachment-file-name="154 KB" data-preview-attachment-id="Attachment_38575846" data-preview-attachment-index="0"><div class="js-active-attachment-preview"><a id="9b0606cab6b12c62b8c2613de3a04a55" rel="nofollow" data-download="{&quot;attachment_id&quot;:38575846,&quot;asset_id&quot;:1946455,&quot;asset_type&quot;:&quot;Work&quot;,&quot;always_allow_download&quot;:2,&quot;track&quot;:null,&quot;button_location&quot;:&quot;swp-preview-selector-dropdown&quot;,&quot;source&quot;:null,&quot;hide_modal&quot;:null}" class="" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20220418015302/https://www.academia.edu/attachments/38575846/download_file?st=MTY1MDI0Njc4MywyMDcuMjQxLjIyOS4xNDg%3D&amp;s=swp-preview-selector-dropdown"><span class="u-tcGrayDarker js-preview-attachment-title" data-preview-attachment-id="Attachment_38575846">Alvandi_2010_BJMES.pdf</span><span class="fa-stack u-floatRight u-ml2x"><i class="fa fa-square fa-stack-2x u-tcGreen"></i><i class="fa fa-stack-1x fa-inverse fa-arrow-down"></i></span></a></div></div></div><div class="u-p2x"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20220418015302/http://www.tandfonline.com/eprint/ceNFMi9d5h85T32gDbGZ/full" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"><span class="u-tcGrayDarker js-preview-attachment-title" data-preview-attachment-id="">www.tandfonline.com/ep...</span><span class="fa-stack u-floatRight u-ml2x"><i class="fa fa-square fa-stack-2x u-tcBlue"></i><i class="fa fa-stack-1x fa-inverse fa-link"></i></span></a></div></div></li></ul></div></div></div><div class="js-swp-work-toolbar expanded-top-card--work-toolbar"><div class="clearfix"><div class="hidden-xs"></div><div class="btn-toolbar js-expanded-top-card--btn-toolbar expanded-top-card--btn-toolbar expanded-top-card--btn-toolbar-button u-displayFlex u-verticalAlignMiddle u-pt3x" style="width:100%"><div class="js-expanded-top-card--visible